hat even protoplanets with Earth-mass cores may keep their hydrogen envelopes\nduring their whole lifetime. In contrast to lower mass protoplanets,\n`super-Earths' accumulate a huge amount of nebula gas and lose only tiny\nfractions of their primordial envelopes. Our results agree with the fact that\nVenus, Earth, and Mars are not surrounded by dense hydrogen envelopes, as well\nas with the recent discoveries of low density `super-Earths' that most likely\ncould not get rid of their protoatmospheres.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 13 Jan 2014 09:31:18 GMT"}],"update_date":"2014-03-05"}
